gs sell under hold over buy number of ratings  full ratings  reasons to store some pure storage in your portfolio may   at  pm et on benzingacom silicon valley is toast according to this analyst mar   at  am et on benzingacom these  stocks could drop  nov   at  am et on benzingacom competitors name chg  market cap seagate technology plc  b smartmetric inc  m unifiedonline inc  m tintri inc  m competitor data provided by partner content trending tickers powered by amzn  spy  uvxy  aapl  wdc  advanced search stocks columns authors topics no results found video center learn morestoryful a division of news corp which owns marketwatch is a leading social media services company headquartered in dublin ireland storyful combines world class journalism with industryleading technology to discover verify and acquire original content and provide the ontheground sources news and media organizations need to tell the stories that matter to their audience pure storage  wikipedia pure storage from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search pure storage type public traded as nyse pstg industry data storage founded  headquarters mountain view california key people ceo scott dietzen cofounder john colgrove cofounder john hayes cfo tim riitters website wwwpurestoragecom pure storage is a mountain view californiabased enterprise data flash storage company founded in  contents  history  flasharray  flashblade  awards  references  external links historyedit in october  the company was founded as os by john colgrove and john hayes mike speiser of sutter hill ventures was an early board member it raised a  million series a round led by sutter hill in august  it raised another  million led by greylock partners with participation by sutter hill scott dietzen former president and cto of zimbra acquired by vmware in january  and former cto of bea systems became chief executive in october  in august  the company announced an investment from the venturecapital arm of samsung electronics which along with redpoint ventures contributed to a  million series c funding round vice president of engineering bob wood joined at that time from omneon acquired by harmonic inc in august  pure storage raised  million in series d funding round led by index ventures partner mike volpi along with existing investors an investment of undisclosed amount from inqtel associated with the us central intelligence agency was announced in may  another investment round e of  million was announced in august  including t rowe price and tiger global management in october  emc corporation filed lawsuits against several former sales employees who left to join pure storage a  million series f funding round closed in april  tim riitters a former google exec joined as chief financial officer cfo in august  on october   pure storage priced their initial public offering at  per share raising about  million it started trading on the new york stock exchange with the symbol pstg flasharrayedit pure storage released a flash memory product called flasharray on august   deployed in a data center flasharray is marketed to accelerate applications like server virtualization desktop virtualization database systems and cloud computing that required very high rates of random io operations per second infiniband technology connected controllers and fibre channel connected to server computers the second generation flasharray released on may   included new software and an enhanced data integrity fabric it was promoted with higher resiliency encryption with zero key management a new web user interface command line interface and support for vmwares vstorage interface in august  the firm released new software features including iscsi connectivity using  gigabit ethernet snapshots and integration with vmware vcenter pure storage used multilevel cell flash memory which has higher capacity for the same price than singlelevel cell memory at the cost of increased wear on and reduced life expectancy of the cells using software such as data compression known as data deduplication the firm markets the flasharray to compete with traditional rotating disk arrays the company estimated flasharray required about  of the power and space required for traditional arrays the firms flash memory is packaged in shelves of solid state memory devices ssds from two known suppliers stec inc and samsung flashbladeedit flashblade is pures second allflash offering designed for highperformance workloads awardsedit in  pure storage was awarded the best place to work by the san francisco business times in the large companies category pure storage was named as silver winner in the wall street journal  technology innovation awards pure storage and samsung won one of two awards for enterprise business applications at an august  flash memory trade show pure storage was selected for the red herring top  americas award in  pure storage was named one of  hot emerging companies by crn magazine in may  pure storage was among the top  best places to work in silicon valley of companies with  employees by the san francisco business times pure storage announced it was a silver winner of the enterprise product of the year in best in biz awards  referencesedit  a b pure storage breaks cost barrier to mainstream flash adoption with first allflash enterprise storage array press release pure storage august   retrieved august     form d notice of exempt offering of securities us securities and exchange commission november   retrieved september     om malik october   zimbra executive heads to hot storage startup giga om retrieved september     don clark august   startup places pure bet on flash memory wall street journal digits blog retrieved august     bob wood to head engineering for pure storage press release summary silicon valleysan jose business journal august   retrieved august     pure storage receives m cash infusion to accelerate explosive growth initiate european expansion press release pure storage